ch at Teachers College. Before launching his career in Education Technology, Daoquan was a programer at General Motors, Shanghai Jiao Tong University, and the Connecticut State Education Resource Center. He has expertise in website and software design as well as extensive knowledge of the graduate student market and graduate recruiting practices. Daoquan received a B.E. from Shanghai Jiao Tong University in 2003, an M.S. in Applied Statistics from Columbia University in 2009, and an Ed.D. in Education Technology and Media from Columbia University in 2012.\n\n</div>\n<div id=\"zp\">\n&nbsp;\n&nbsp;\n[ms_divider style=\"dashed\" align=\"center\" width=\"100%\" margin_top=\"30px\" margin_bottom=\"30px\" border_size=\"\" border_color=\"\" icon=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\n<h3 class=\"page-title-h3\">Ping Zhang, Ph.D.,</h3>\n<h3 class=\"page-title-h3\" style=\"font-size: 1.1rem;color: #888888;font-weight:300;\">Director of Development</h3>\n&nbsp;\n\n<div><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-527 teampic\" src=\"http://www.gridet.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/zhangping500-300x300.png\" alt=\"zhangping500\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" /></div>\nPing Zhang manages the development and maintenance of all products and services. His expertise are in web product development and front and back design. Ping Zhang previously worked at the Cloud Based Computing Center at Amazon from 2011 to 2016. He received his B.E. from Beijing institute of Technology in 2003 and his PhD in Computer Science from Purdue University in 2011.\n\n</div>\n<div id=\"wy\">\n&nbsp;\n&nbsp;\n[ms_divider style=\"dashed\" align=\"center\" width=\"100%\" margin_top=\"30px\" margin_bottom=\"30px\" border_size=\"\" border_color=\"\" icon=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\n<h3 class=\"page-title-h3\">Vivian Wang, M.A.,</h3>\n<h3 class=\"page-title-h3\" style=\"font-size: 1.1rem;color: #888888;font-weight:300;\">Knowledge Director</h3>\n&nbsp;\n\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-526 teampic\" src=\"http://www.gridet.com/wp-co