ur client’s program website with that of its direct competitors to provide recommendations for improvement so that clients stay abreast of how competing programs market themselves. The enhancement report is grouped around 6 key areas that we have identified as game changers for successful recruitment. These range from general stylistic issues commonly found in the program introduction to more granular, detailed information such as scholarship information, credit transfer policies and so forth.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOur Upgrid service is <i>not</i> just a one time service. Once we have provided the “whoops” and enhancement reports, we will continue to update the information daily until the the contract expiration date (typically the end of the academic year). Our account managers are also available on demand to answer client questions and address any concerns that arise during the service delivery process.','Upgrid Service','','inherit','closed','closed','','69-revision-v1','','','2016-06-28 01:35:48','2016-06-28 05:35:48','',69,'http://www.gridet.com/69-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(362,1,'2016-06-25 15:55:28','2016-06-25 19:55:28','<h2>Upgrid Consulting</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<hr>\r\n&nbsp;\r\nUpgrid is a website content review research and consulting service offered by GET to graduate institutions throughout the United States. Graduate program websites are one of the most important tools for attracting and recruiting prospective graduate students. The Upgrid service is designed to help you maximize the potential returns of an informative and easy-to-navigate website. We will review your program website, as well as the websites of your competitors, and collate our findings into two types of easily digestible consulting reports.\r\n&nbsp;\r\n[ms_divider style=\"dashed\" align=\"center\" width=\"100%\" margin_top=\"30px\" margin_bottom=\"30px\" border_size=\"\" border_color=\"\" icon=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\r\n<h3 style=\"font-size: 28px;\">The “whoops” report</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\nThe first type of report is focused on resolving technical and informational issues that prevent prospective students from obtaining the information they are looking for. By conducting detailed reviews of thousands of graduate program websites, we are experts in the industry standards, and can help you avoid common problems such as dead links, infinite loops, and outdated information.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n[ms_divider style=\"dashed\" align=\"center\" width=\"100%\" margin_top=\"30px\" margin_bottom=\"30px\" border_size=\"\" border_color=\"\" icon=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\r\n<h3 style=\"font-size: 28px;\">The enhancement report</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe second type of report compares our client’s program website with that of its direct competitors to provide recommendations for improvement so that clients stay abreast of how competing programs market themselves. The enhancement report is grouped around 6 key areas that we have identified as game changers for successful recruitment. These range from general stylistic issues commonly found in the program introduction to more granular, detailed information such as scholarship information, credit transfer policies and so forth.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOur Upgrid service is <i>not</i> just a one time service. Once we have provided the “whoops” and enhancement reports, we will continue to update the information daily until the the contract expiration date (typically the end of the academic year). Our account managers are also available on demand to answer client questions and address any concerns that arise during the service delivery process.','Upgrid Service','','inherit','closed','closed','','69-revision-v1','','','2016-06-25 15:55:28','2016-06-25 19:55:28','',69,'http://www.gridet.com/69-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(406,1,'2016-06-28 01:36:35','2016-06-28 05:36:35','<h2>About</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"who-we-are\">\r\n\r\n<h3>Who We Are</h3>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span>Gridology Education &amp; Technology Inc. (GET), was established in 2016 by a group of Columbia University alumni who shared a vision for a more connected and efficient graduate application process. From the initial question “what should I study in grad school?” to finally ascending the podium and shaking the president’s hand, we have all experienced the challenges of obtaining a higher degree. We want to make this process easier and more navigable than ever before. By connecting students to schools and schools to students, we strive every day to help people make the choices that will fulfill their dreams and ambitions. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span>Compared with the accessible and streamlined resources available to prospective undergraduates, efficient and digestible information about graduate schools can be surprisingly difficult to locate. Until now! Our rapidly expanding database gradgrid.com provides detailed information that you need about thousands of graduate programs at top universities. By providing an efficient, centralized, and customizable research tool, we are revolutionizing the graduate application process.</span>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n[ms_divider style=\"dashed\" align=\"center\" width=\"100%\" margin_top=\"30px\" margin_bottom=\"30px\" border_size=\"\" border_color=\"\" icon=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div id=\"mission\">\r\n<h3>Mission</h3>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span>Our mission is to facilitate communication between graduate institutions and advanced degree seekers across the globe. As more people than ever before pursue graduate studies, effective digital communication is critical to rise above the competition. This entrepreneurial challenge has inspired our vision of a smooth and seamless graduate application cycle where the priorities of students and schools are perfectly synchronized every step of the way. Each of our products and services is focussed on filling an aspect of the information gap between schools and students and allowing them to make informed and strategic decisions about where to apply and who to recruit.  </span>\r\n</div>','About','','inherit','closed','closed','','106-revision-v1','','','2016-06-28 01:36:35','2016-06-28 05:36:35','',106,'http://www.gridet.com/106-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(363,1,'2016-06-25 15:56:04','2016-06-25 19:56:04','<h2>About</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"who-we-are\">\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"font-size: 28px;\">Who We Are</h3>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span>Gridology Education &amp; Technology Inc. (GET), was established in 2016 by a group of Columbia University alumni who shared a vision for a more connected and efficient graduate application process. From the initial question “what should I study in grad school?” to finally ascending the podium and shaking the president’s hand, we have all experienced the challenges of obtaining a higher degree. We want to make this process easier and more navigable than ever before. By connecting students to schools and schools to students, we strive every day to help people make the choices that will fulfill their dreams and ambitions. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span>Compared with the accessible and streamlined resources available to prospective undergraduates, efficient and digestible information about graduate schools can be surprisingly difficult to locate. Until now! Our rapidly expanding database gradgrid.com provides detailed information that you need about thousands of graduate programs at top universities. By providing an efficient, centralized, and customizable research tool, we are revolutionizing the graduate application process.</span>\r\n</div>\r\n[ms_divider style=\"dashed\" align=\"center\" width=\"100%\" margin_top=\"30px\" margin_bottom=\"30px\" border_size=\"\" border_color=\"\" icon=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div id=\"mission\">\r\n<h3 style=\"font-size: 28px;\">Mission </span></h3>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span>Our mission is to facilitate communication between graduate institutions and advanced de