idaoquan-300x300.jpg\" border_radius=\"15px\" link=\"\" link_target=\"_blank\" light_box=\"no\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\nDaoquan Li is the founder and Chief Executive Officer of GET, he currently oversees all business operations and fundraising activities for the company. Between 2012 and 2016 Daoquan worked in graduate student enrollment at Columbia University, where he led the enrollment research at Teachers College. Before launching his career in Education Technology, Daoquan was a programer at General Motors, Shanghai Jiao Tong University, and the Connecticut State Education Resource Center. He has expertise in website and software design as well as extensive knowledge of the graduate student market and graduate recruiting practices. Daoquan received a B.E. from Shanghai Jiao Tong University in 2003, an M.A. in Applied Statistics from Columbia University in 2009, and an Ed.D. in Education Technology and Media from Columbia University in 2012.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"zp\">\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n[ms_divider style=\"dashed\" align=\"center\" width=\"100%\" margin_top=\"30px\" margin_bottom=\"30px\" border_size=\"\" border_color=\"\" icon=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"font-size: 25px;\">Ping Zhang, Ph.D., Director of Development</h3>\r\n\r\n[ms_image_frame src=\"http://www.gridet.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/zhangping-300x300.png\" border_radius=\"15px\" link=\"\" link_target=\"_blank\" light_box=\"no\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\nPing Zhang is a founding member and Development Director at GET, he manages the development and maintenance of all products and services. His expertise are in web product development and front and back design. Ping Zhang previously worked at the Cloud Based Computing Center at Amazon from 2011 to 2016. He received his B.E. from Beijing institute of Technology in 2003 and his PhD in Computer Science from Purdue University in 2011.\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"wy\">\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n[ms_divider style=\"dashed\" align=\"center\" width=\"100%\" margin_top=\"30px\" margin_bottom=\"30px\" border_size=\"\" border_color=\"\" icon=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"font-size: 25px;\">Vivian Wang, M.A., Knowledge Director</h3>\r\n\r\n[ms_image_frame src=\"http://www.gridet.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/wangyu-300x300.jpg\" border_radius=\"15px\" link=\"\" link_target=\"_blank\" light_box=\"no\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\nYu Wang is a founding member and knowledge director at GET, she manages the Gradgrid database and oversees a team of knowledge experts. She has extensive professional experience in graduate recruitment, program management, teaching, and advising at universities throughout the world. Yu Wang previously served as the international program coordinator first at Xiamen University from 2013 to 2014 and then at Columbia University in 2015. She received a B.A. in Administrative Management from Beijing Electronic Science University in 2009 and an M.A. in Simultaneous Interpreting from Newcastle University in 2010.\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"vb\">\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n[ms_divider style=\"dashed\" align=\"center\" width=\"100%\" margin_top=\"30px\" margin_bottom=\"30px\" border_size=\"\" border_color=\"\" icon=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"font-size: 25px;\">Virgil Bisio, M.A., Director of Marketing</h3>\r\n\r\n[ms_image_frame src=\"http://www.gridet.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/virgil-300x300.jpg\" border_radius=\"15px\" link=\"\" link_target=\"_blank\" light_box=\"no\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\nVirgilio Bisio is currently the director of marketing at GET, he supervises sales, marketing, and client services. From 2012 to 2014 Virgilio worked in operations management for Payton Technology. He received an B.A. in History from Trinity College in 2012 and an M.A. in East Asian Languages and Cultures from Columbia University in 2016.\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"mn\">\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n[ms_divider style=\"dashed\" align=\"center\" width=\"100%\" margin_top=\"30px\" margin_bottom=\"30px\" border_size=\"\" border_color=\"\" icon=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"font-size: 25px;\">Michael Nusbaum, M.A., Product Manager</h3>\r\n\r\n[ms_image_frame src=\"http://www.gridet.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/michael-300x300.jpg\" border_radius=\"15px\" link=\"\" link_target=\"_blank\" light_box=\"no\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\nMichael Nusbaum is currently the Product Manager at GET, he oversees all research activities and collaborates product development team to generate product creation and development strategies. Michael previously worked as a Program Manager first for Fuzhou University and then for the Shenzhen Research Institute at Xiamen University. He received his B.A. from Rutgers in 2006 and an M.A. in East Asian Languages and Cultures from Columbia University in 2014.\r\n</div>','Leadership','','inherit','closed','closed','','108-revision-v1','','','2016-06-26 13:31:55','2016-06-26 17:31:55','',108,'http://www.gridet.com/108-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(380,1,'2016-06-26 13:32:32','2016-06-26 17:32:32','<div id=\"ldq\">\r\n<h2>Leadership</h2>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 style=\"font-size: 1rem;\">Daoquan Li, Ed.D., CEO</h3>\r\n\r\n[ms_image_frame src=\"http://www.gridet.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/lidaoquan-300x300.jpg\" border_radius=\"15px\" link=\"\" link_target=\"_blank\" light_box=\"no\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\nDaoquan Li is the founder and Chief Executive Officer of GET, he currently oversees all business operations and fundraising activities for the company. Between 2012 and 2016 Daoquan worked in graduate student enrollment at Columbia University, where he led the enrollment research at Teachers College. Before launching his career in Education Technology, Daoquan was a programer at General Mot