 in grad school?” to finally ascending the podium and shaking the president’s hand, we have all experienced the challenges of obtaining a higher degree. We want to make this process easier and more navigable than ever before. By connecting students to schools and schools to students, we strive every day to help people make the choices that will fulfill their dreams and ambitions.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nCompared with the accessible and streamlined resources available to prospective undergraduates, efficient and digestible information about graduate schools can be surprisingly difficult to locate and organize. Until now! Our rapidly expanding database gradgrid.com provides detailed information that you need about thousands of graduate programs at top universities. By providing an efficient, centralized, and customizable research tool, we are revolutionizing the graduate application process.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[ms_divider style=\"dashed\" align=\"center\" width=\"100%\" margin_top=\"30px\" margin_bottom=\"30px\" border_size=\"\" border_color=\"\" icon=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\r\n<div id=\"mission\">\r\n<h3 class=\"page-title-h3\">Mission</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOur mission is to facilitate communication between graduate institutions and advanced degree seekers across the globe. As more people than ever before pursue graduate studies, effective digital communication is critical to rise above the competition. This entrepreneurial challenge has inspired our vision of a smooth and seamless graduate application cycle where the priorities of students and schools are perfectly synchronized every step of the way. Each of our products and services is focussed on filling an aspect of the information gap between schools and students and allowing them to make informed and strategic decisions about where to apply and who to recruit.\r\n\r\n</div>','About','','inherit','closed','closed','','106-revision-v1','','','2016-06-30 01:12:58','2016-06-30 05:12:58','',106,'http://www.gridet.com/106-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(434,1,'2016-06-28 18:26:43','2016-06-28 22:26:43','<h2 class=\"page-title-h2\">About</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<br/>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div id=\"who-we-are\">\r\n<h3 class=\"page-title-h3\">Who We Are</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nGridology Education &amp; Technology, Inc. (GET), was established in 2016 by a group of Columbia University alumni who shared a vision for a more connected and efficient graduate application process. From the initial question “what should I study in grad school?” to finally ascending the podium and shaking the president’s hand, we have all experienced the challenges of obtaining a higher degree. We want to make this process easier and more navigable than ever before. By connecting students to schools and schools to students, we strive every day to help people make the choices that will fulfill their dreams and ambitions.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nCompared with the accessible and streamlined resources available to prospective undergraduates, efficient and digestible information about graduate schools can be surprisingly difficult to locate and organize. Until now! Our rapidly expanding database gradgrid.com provides detailed information that you need about thousands of graduate programs at top universities. By providing an efficient, centralized, and customizable research tool, we are revolutionizing the graduate application process.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[ms_divider style=\"dashed\" align=\"center\" width=\"100%\" margin_top=\"30px\" margin_bottom=\"30px\" border_size=\"\" border_color=\"\" icon=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\r\n<div id=\"mission\">\r\n<h3 class=\"page-title-h3\">Mission</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOur mission is to facilitate communication between graduate institutions and advanced degree seekers across the globe. As more people than ever before pursue graduate studies, effective digital communication is critical to rise above the competition. This entrepreneurial challenge has inspired our vision of a smooth and seamless graduate application cycle where the priorities of students and schools are perfectly synchronized every step of the way. Each of our products and services is focussed on filling an aspect of the information gap between schools and students and allowing them to make informed and strategic decisions about where to apply and who to recruit.\r\n\r\n</div>','About','','inherit','closed','closed','','106-revision-v1','','','2016-06-28 18:26:43','2016-06-28 22:26:43','',106,'http://www.gridet.com/106-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(435,1,'2016-06-28 18:27:26','2016-06-28 22:27:26','<div id=\"ldq\">\r\n<h2 class=\"page-title-h2\">Leadership</h2>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 class=\"page-title-h3\">Daoquan Li, Ed.D., CEO</h3>\r\n\r\n[ms_image_frame src=\"http://www.gridet.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/lidaoquan-300x300.jpg\" border_radius=\"15px\" link=\"\" link_target=\"_blank\" light_box=\"no\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\nDaoquan Li is the founder and Chief Executive Officer of GET, he currently oversees all business operations and fundraising activities for the company. Between 2012 and 2016 Daoquan worked in graduate student enrollment at Columbia University, where he led the enrollment research at Teachers College. Before launching his career in Education Technology, Daoquan was a programer at General Motors, Shanghai Jiao Tong University, and the Connecticut State Education Resource Center. He has expertise in website and software design as well as extensive knowledge of the graduate student market and graduate recruiting practices. Daoquan received a B.E. from Shanghai Jiao Tong University in 2003, an M.S. in Applied Statistics from Columbia University in 2009, and an Ed.D. in Education Technology and Media from Columbia University in 2012.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"zp\">\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n[ms_divider style=\"dashed\" align=\"center\" width=\"100%\" margin_top=\"30px\" margin_bottom=\"30px\" border_siz