 internet for information that will help them sift through the thousands of programs offered by U.S. graduate schools. The Gradgrid database is an advanced, centralized search engine, exclusively devoted to helping applicants find and research programs that interest them.  Both search functions and results are easily customizable. Search results are organized in the ‘grid’ view for easy access and comparison. Your ‘grid’ also allows to customize the information by adding notes and comments of your own.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 500; \">Launching schedule:</span> <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Fall 2016 </span>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 500;\">Welcome to <a id=\"bookmark-this\"></a>bookmark and visit us back!</span>','Gradgrid service','','inherit','closed','closed','','71-revision-v1','','','2016-06-30 00:44:23','2016-06-30 04:44:23','',71,'http://www.gridet.com/71-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(461,1,'2016-06-29 17:17:46','2016-06-29 21:17:46','<h2 class=\"page-title-h2\">Gradgrid Graduate Programs Database</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<br/>\r\nIf you went to college in the United States, you are probably familiar with college guidebooks, campus tours, and college guidance counselors. Unfortunately for graduate school applicants, such resources are only part of the norm. Compared with the accessible and streamlined resources available to prospective undergraduates, efficient and digestible information about graduate schools can be surprisingly difficult to locate or organize. The reasons are many. For Example, the graduate programs that you might be interested in, or match your backgrounds could be many, even in different academic fields. To make the best decision, most of the serious degree seekers would dig into the nitty-gritty information and piece the puzzles together.\r\n\r\nOur Gradgrid Database is a free and convenient cloud based solution to the problem of deciding which graduate schools are right for you. Prospective gr