ram website with that of its direct competitors to provide recommendations for improvement so that clients stay abreast of how competing programs market themselves. The enhancement report is grouped around 6 key areas that we have identified as game changers for successful recruitment. These range from general stylistic issues commonly found in the program introduction to more granular, detailed information such as scholarship information, credit transfer policies and so forth.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOur Upgrid service is <i>not</i> just a one time service, but a SaaS (software as a Service). Once we have provided the “whoops” and enhancement reports, we will continue to update the information daily until the contract expiration date (typically the end of the academic year). Our account managers are also available on demand to answer client questions and address any concerns that arise during the service delivery process.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gridet.com/contact\">Request a demo</a>','Upgrid Service','','inherit','closed','closed','','69-revision-v1','','','2016-06-30 01:00:01','2016-06-30 05:00:01','',69,'http://www.gridet.com/69-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(477,1,'2016-06-30 01:00:41','2016-06-30 05:00:41','<h2 class=\"page-title-h2\">Upgrid Consulting - Software as a Service</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\nUpgrid is a website content review, research and consulting service offered by GET to graduate institutions throughout the United States. Graduate program websites are one of the most important tools for attracting and recruiting prospective graduate students. The Upgrid service is designed to help you maximize the potential returns of an informative and easy-to-navigate website. We will review your program website, as well as the websites of your competitors, and collate our findings into two types of easily digestible consulting reports in the client\'s’ web portal created by GET.\r\n\r\n[ms_divider style=\"dashed\" align=\"center\" 