eekers would dig into the nitty-gritty information and piece the puzzles together.\r\n&nbsp;\r\nOur Gradgrid Database is a free and convenient cloud based solution to the problem of deciding which graduate schools are right for you. Prospective graduate students routinely spend weeks or even months searching the internet for information that will help them sift through the thousands of programs offered by U.S. graduate schools. The Gradgrid database is an advanced, centralized search engine, exclusively devoted to helping applicants find and research programs that interest them.  Both search functions and results are easily customizable. Search results are organized in the ‘grid’ view for easy access and comparison. Your ‘grid’ also allows to customize the information by adding notes and comments of your own.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 500; \">Launching schedule: Fall 2016 </span>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 500;\">Welcome to <a id=\"bookmark-this\"><i class=\"fa fa-bookmark lg\"></i>&nbsp;bookmark</a> and visit us back!</span>','Gradgrid service','','inherit','closed','closed','','71-revision-v1','','','2016-07-01 11:09:40','2016-07-01 15:09:40','',71,'http://www.gridet.com/71-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(590,1,'2016-07-01 11:21:19','2016-07-01 15:21:19','<h2 class=\"page-title-h2\">Upgrid Consulting - Software as a Service</h2>\r\n<hr />\r\n&nbsp;\r\nUpgrid is a website content review, research and consulting service offered by GET to graduate institutions throughout the United States. Graduate program websites are one of the most important tools for attracting and recruiting prospective graduate students. The Upgrid service is designed to help you maximize the potential returns of an informative and easy-to-navigate website. We will review your program website, as well as the websites of your competitors, and collate our findings into two types of easily digestible consulting reports in the client\'s’ web portal created by GET.\r\n\r\n[ms_divider style=\"dashed\" align=\"center\" width=\"100%\" margin_top=\"30px\" margin_bottom=\"30px\" border_size=\"\" border_color=\"\" icon=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\r\n<h3 class=\"page-title-h3\">The “whoops” report</h3>\r\n\r\nThe first type of report is focused on resolving technical and informational issues that prevent prospective students from obtaining the information they are looking for. By conducting detailed reviews of thousands of graduate program websites, we are experts in the industry standards, and can help you avoid common problems such as typo, dead links, infinite loops, outdated information, inconsistencies, floating pages, dysfunctional menu or sidebars and confusing information.\r\n[ms_divider style=\"dashed\" align=\"center\" width=\"100%\" margin_top=\"30px\" margin_bottom=\"30px\" border_size=\"\" border_color=\"\" icon=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\r\n<h3 class=\"page-title-h3\">The enhancement report</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe second type of report compares our client’s program website with that of its direct competitors to provide recommendations for improvement so that clients stay abreast of how competing programs market themselves. The enhancement report is grouped around 6 key areas that we have identified as game changers for successful recruitment. These range from general stylistic issues commonly found in the program introduction to more granular, detailed information such as scholarship information, credit transfer policies and so forth.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOur Upgrid service is <i>not</i> just a one time service, but a SaaS (Software as a Service). Once we have provided the “whoops” and enhancement reports, we will continue to update the information daily until the contract expiration date (typically the end of the academic year). Our account managers are also available on demand to answer client questions and address any concerns that arise during the service delivery process.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.gridet.com/contact\" style=\"font-weight:500;\"><i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o \" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>&nbsp;Request a demo</a>','Upgrid Service','','inherit','closed','closed','','69-revision-v1','','','2016-07-01 11:21:19','2016-07-01 15:21:19','',69,'http://www.gridet.com/69-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(591,1,'2016-07-02 17:11:22','2016-07-02 21:11:22','<div id=\"ldq\">\r\n<h2 class=\"page-title-h2\">Leadership</h2>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 class=\"page-title-h3\">Daoquan Li, Ed.D.,</h3>\r\n<h3 class=\"page-title-h3\" style=\"font-size: 1.1rem; color: #888888; font-weight:300;\">CEO</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-523 teampic\" src=\"http://www.gridet.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/lidaoquan500-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"lidaoquan500\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" /></div>\r\nDaoquan Li currently oversees all business operations and fundraising activities for the company. Between 2012 and 2016 Daoquan worked in graduate student enrollment at Columbia University, where he led the enrollment research at Teachers College. Before launching his career in Education Technology, Daoquan was a programer at General Motors, Shanghai Jiao Tong University, and the Connecticut State Education Resource Center. He has expertise in website and software design as well as extensive knowledge of the graduate student market and graduate recruiting practices. Daoquan received a B.E. from Shanghai Jiao Tong University in 2003, an M.S. in Applied Statistics from Columbia University in 2009, and an Ed.D. in Education Technology and Media from Columbia University in 2012.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"zp\">\r\n&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;\r\n[ms_divider style=\"dashed\" align=\"center\" width=\"100%\" margin_top=\"30px\" margin_bottom=\"30px\" border_size=\"\" border_color=\"\" icon=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]\r\n<h3 class=\"page-title-h3\">Ping Zhang, Ph.D.,</h3>\r\n<h3 class=\"page-title-h3\" style=\"font-size: 1.1rem;color: #888888;\">Director of Development</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<div><i